the Organ Transplant Center quickly.

382
00:29:22,890 --> 00:29:23,890
Hmm.

383
00:29:24,390 --> 00:29:25,390
What?

384
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:27,520
Is there a problem with that?

385
00:29:28,930 --> 00:29:30,150
No, I just think...

386
00:29:31,570 --> 00:29:34,900
it will be difficult to reopen
the center after all.

387
00:29:35,630 --> 00:29:36,770
What are you talking about?

388
00:29:37,240 --> 00:29:40,480
We agreed on it when we renewed
Dr. Kang's contract.

389
00:29:40,950 --> 00:29:42,630
What are you talking about?

390
00:29:42,900 --> 00:29:45,670
Not one of you reviewed
the contract thoroughly?

391
00:29:48,730 --> 00:29:49,850
<i>It's your contract.</i>

392
00:29:49,850 --> 00:29:52,330
<i>I inserted the clause regarding
the Organ Transplant Center.</i>

393
00:29:56,930 --> 00:29:57,930
Look.

394
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:11,810
- There's no clause.
- No way.

395
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:21,140
Where is Miss Bae now?

396
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:25,760
I'll find her.

397
00:30:30,420 --> 00:30:32,890
Mr. Chairman Song, what are you doing?

398
00:30:32,890 --> 00:30:35,860
He signed a contract without a clause
about the Organ Transplant Center.

399
00:30:35,860 --> 00:30:38,470
Our counterparty has refused
this condition from the start.

400
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:42,970
So you've deceived us from the start?

401
00:30:42,970 --> 00:30:43,970
Myeong Hee.

402
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:45,720
I'm a businessman.

403
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:47,290
I'm not a philanthropist.

404
00:30:47,290 --> 00:30:48,340
We're friends...

405
00:30:48,340 --> 00:30:51,110
...but I can't continue to invest
in this sinking hospital.

406
00:30:51,110 --> 00:30:53,660
How many times did I tell you
not to believe him?

407
00:30:53,660 --> 00:30:55,480
It's your fault, man.

408
00:30:55,480 --> 00:30:56,460
What?

409
00:30:56,460 --> 00:30:57,880
If you hadn't needed disciplining...

410
00:30:57,880 --> 00:31:00,000
...the hospital wouldn't be
in this situation.

411
00:31:02,340 --> 00:31:03,340
Fine.

412
00:31:09,390 --> 00:31:12,180
[Hae Gil Hospital]

413
00:31:15,460 --> 00:31:16,460
Ji Won.

414
00:31:17,030 --> 00:31:17,830
Yes.

415
00:31:17,830 --> 00:31:19,690
Did you have me sign a contract...

416
00:31:19,690 --> 00:31:22,400
...without inserting the clause
about the Organ Transplant Center?

417
00:31:22,850 --> 00:31:24,010
Did you deceive me?

418
00:31:24,710 --> 00:31:25,710
No.

419
00:31:26,970 --> 00:31:30,040
This is the contract you signed.

420
00:31:31,840 --> 00:31:34,840
The contract Chairman
Song has is a fake.

421
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:37,720
I forged your signature on it...

422
00:31:38,870 --> 00:31:41,120
so don't act too shocked.

423
00:31:42,830 --> 00:31:45,280
If Chairman Song pulls out
of the hospital...

424
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:47,340
there will be financial
issues, but...

425
00:31:47,340 --> 00:31:48,470
Why did you do it?

426
00:31:53,640 --> 00:31:56,140
[Letter of resignation]

427
00:31:54,040 --> 00:31:56,140
This is my letter of resignation.

428
00:31:56,300 --> 00:31:57,970
Can you deliver it to Ms. Chairman?

429
00:31:57,970 --> 00:31:59,640
I asked you why you did it, Ji Won.

430
00:32:02,220 --> 00:32:04,600
When Chairman Song finds out
what you did...

431
00:32:05,670 --> 00:32:09,080
and you're caught forging documents,
you could be in trouble too.

432
00:32:09,080 --> 00:32:11,190
That didn't matter to me...

433
00:32:12,770 --> 00:32:14,860
as long as I could help you.

434
00:32:18,490 --> 00:32:19,920
I wished...

435
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:24,230
you would leave this hospital
with Chairman Song.

436
00:32:26,290 --> 00:32:27,770
If you had...

437
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:33,540
my feelings for you...

438
00:32:34,490 --> 00:32:36,610
would never have
been revealed to you.

439
00:32:51,030 --> 00:32:53,250
Here's brown rice...

440
00:32:53,250 --> 00:32:55,380
...and less salty soup.

441
00:32:55,830 --> 00:32:58,730
They're all healthy dishes.

442
00:33:00,330 --> 00:33:01,860
Now...

443
00:33:01,860 --> 00:33:03,110
...is that everything?

444
00:33:06,390 --> 00:33:07,600
Thank you.

445
00:33:08,210 --> 00:33:11,070
I really like it when someone
fixes me a meal.

446
00:33:11,070 --> 00:33:12,800
I know that.

447
00:33:13,070 --> 00:33:14,270
Let's eat.

448
00:33:16,140 --> 00:33:18,490
Did you wash your hands before cooking?

449
00:33:18,490 --> 00:33:21,690
Yes, of course.
I even used a spoon to taste the soup...

450
00:33:21,690 --> 00:33:23,910
and I didn't put it back
in the soup pot either.

451
00:33:23,910 --> 00:33:25,180
Trust me.

452
00:33:28,230 --> 00:33:30,870
The farmers, the fishermen,
sunshine and...

453
00:33:32,580 --> 00:33:33,870
- What else?
- The rain.

454
00:33:33,870 --> 00:33:34,970
Yes, the rain.

455
00:33:34,970 --> 00:33:36,680
Thank you for the meal.

456
00:33:41,270 --> 00:33:42,200
Mmm...

457
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:43,340
It tastes good.

458
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:48,920
